	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Lagrange Point translation</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><ul><li>Cornarea/Corn Area (AG's <em>Lagrange Point</em> translation) </li></ul><br />On the one hand, there exist <a href="http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/lagrangepoint/lagrangepoint.htm" class="postlink">other <em>FF</em> allusions in <em>LP</em></a>. But on the other hand, <a href="http://www.gamefaqs.com/nes/570557-lagrange-point/faqs/56320" class="postlink">there's also a &quot;Corn Base&quot;</a>.</div><br /><br />We localized a few of the area names a very, very little bit; Cornarea was one of them. There's a Corn Area, Potato Area, and Orange Area, and in localizing we figured we'd give a very slight tilt of the head to other famous similar-sounding names. But all the areas and cities, with the exception of the Isis City capital, are named after the essential building blocks of society - food, minerals, energy.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


